{{Quote|[The Qulun] were no more trustworthy than a bunch of roving, slobbering Alwari, the dorgum-herding snigvolds!|Tooqui employs the 'dorgum' to curse the Qulun camp traders who abducted his Jedi friends|<ref name="The Approaching Storm">''[[The Approaching Storm]]''</ref>}}
The '''dorgum''' was a [[Species/Legends|species]] of domesticated animal that was raised and utilized by the [[Alwari]] of [[Ansion/Legends|Ansion]]. [[Gwurran]] were known to use the creature's name derisively.

In [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]], the bold [[Tooqui]], before launching a personal campaign to rescue his captive [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] friends from a [[Qulun]] [[Qulun camp|camp]], wished himself a piece of dorgum dung when confronted by a pair of snuffling [[kholot]] after he'd escaped down their burrow-hole from his pursuers.

